The paper deals with online scheduling algorithms, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of coordination mechanisms and Nash equilibria also suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their performance, which falls under information theory (cs.IT).
